        see:two source Piers stand with real opus stock — different tracks on each shelf
        see:the listener redeemed an invite from each source — both pairs sealed with live Music grants
        see:the catalog merged at the mirror — husks from both sources carry their chunk promises
        see:the chase began on the cached preview alone — the spool held at the first boundary until the tail ran low
        see:the first streaming ask went out at exactly the segment after the last preview
        see:the playhead crossed the first boundary onto chunks transcoded on demand
        see:the fan-out kept every other preview warm across both sources while the first track played
        see:injected entropy moved the dial — the same seeded state picks differently after the stir
        see:the dial chased to the other Pier — a record from the second source opened on its warm preview
